{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Validate Generated Tests",
  "description": "After any file is created or modified under generated/tests/, automatically runs the feature-appropriate Playwright tests. If tests pass, creates a branch and opens a PR. If tests fail, self-corrects up to 3 times before stopping.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileEdited",
    "patterns": [
      "generated/tests/**/*.spec.ts"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A file under generated/tests/ was just created or modified. Follow these steps exactly.\n\n---\n\n## Step 0 — Detect Feature Name\n\nInspect the path of the file that was just saved.\nThe path format is: `generated/tests/<featureName>/<testFile>.spec.ts`\nExtract `<featureName>` from the path.\n\nDetermine the correct validation command:\n| featureName  | Command |\n|-------------|--------------------------------------------|\n| `client`    | `npm run gen:validate:client`              |\n| `saucedemo` | `npm run gen:validate:saucedemo`           |\n| `conduit`   | `npm run gen:validate:conduit`             |\n| other        | `npx playwright test --project=generated-<featureName> --reporter=list` |\n\nAlso determine:\n- Page Objects directory: `generated/pages/<featureName>/`\n- Tests directory: `generated/tests/<featureName>/`\n- Branch name format: `generated-tests/<featureName>/issue-<N>`\n- Commit scope: only `generated/pages/<featureName>/` and `generated/tests/<featureName>/` (plus `utils/<featureName>/` if it was newly created)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1 — Validate (max 3 attempts)\n\nAttempt 1:\n1. Run the feature-appropriate validate command in `/home/aryaskumar/Kiro/ClientApp`\n2. If all tests PASSED: proceed to Phase 2.\n3. If any test FAILED: show the exact error, diagnose root cause, fix ONLY files under `generated/pages/<featureName>/` or `generated/tests/<featureName>/`, then do Attempt 2.\n\nAttempt 2:\n1. Re-run the same validate command.\n2. If all tests PASSED: proceed to Phase 2.\n3. If any test FAILED: apply a meaningfully different fix to generated files, then do Attempt 3.\n\nAttempt 3 (final):\n1. Re-run the same validate command.\n2. If all tests PASSED: proceed to Phase 2.\n3. If tests STILL FAIL: STOP. Report to the user:\n   - Test file(s) that failed\n   - What was tried across all 3 attempts\n   - Last error message\n   - Why automated fixing could not resolve it\n   - Do NOT proceed to Phase 2. Do NOT attempt a 4th fix.\n\n## Phase 2 — Create PR (only if all tests passed)\n\n1. Determine the GitHub Issue number from the generated test file's comment header (e.g. `GitHub Issue #1`).\n\n2. Create a branch name in the format: `generated-tests/<featureName>/issue-<N>`\n   Run these git commands in `/home/aryaskumar/Kiro/ClientApp`:\n   ```\n   git checkout -b generated-tests/<featureName>/issue-<N>\n   git add generated/pages/<featureName>/ generated/tests/<featureName>/\n   git add utils/<featureName>/   (only if this directory was newly created for this issue)\n   git commit -m \"feat: add generated tests for GitHub Issue #<N> [<featureName>]\"\n   git push -u origin generated-tests/<featureName>/issue-<N>\n   ```\n\n3. Create a pull request using GitHub MCP:\n   - owner: aryaskumar-spec\n   - repo: ClientApp\n   - head: `generated-tests/<featureName>/issue-<N>`\n   - base: main\n   - title: `[Generated][<featureName>] Tests for Issue #<N> — <issue title>`\n   - body: Include:\n     - Link to the GitHub Issue\n     - Feature: `<featureName>`\n     - HIPAA status: SAFE\n     - Page Objects reused (list with full paths)\n     - Page Objects generated (list with full paths)\n     - Tests generated (list with full paths)\n     - Auth utility created (if applicable): `utils/<featureName>/ApiUtils.ts`\n     - Test result: PASSED on attempt <N>\n\n4. Report the PR URL to the user.\n\n## Hard Rules\n- Never modify files under `pages/`, `tests/`, or top-level `utils/*.ts`\n- Only commit files under `generated/pages/<featureName>/`, `generated/tests/<featureName>/`, and `utils/<featureName>/` (if new)\n- Never create a PR if any test is still failing\n- Never mix files from different features in the same commit"
  }
}
